<doc id="263300" wikidata="Q5223224" url="?curid=263300" title="Dark Fantasy (series)">
<text>Dark Fantasy was an American radio supernatural thriller anthology series. It had a short run of 31 episodes, debuting on November 14, 1941, and ending on June 19, 1942. Its writer was Scott Bishop, also known for his work on &quot;The Mysterious Traveler&quot;. It originated from station WKY in Oklahoma City and was heard Friday nights on NBC stations. The stories found a nationwide audience almost immediately.

