==Rankings and reputation==

The 2024 QS World University Rankings ranked the University of Bologna 154th in the world as well as 73rd (1st in Italy, 18th in Europe) with specific reference to academic reputation. In another measurement by the same organization, it was positioned among the world&#x27;s top 100 universities for graduate employability.

In the 2024 Times Higher Education World University Rankings, it claimed the 155th place globally. In the 2023 THE Impact Rankings, which measure the universities&#x27; commitment to sustainable development in compliance with the UN 2030 Agenda, Bologna took 5th place in Europe and 23rd in the world.

Furthermore, Bologna topped Italy&#x27;s 2023 list of large public universities (&gt; 40,000 students), produced by the Italian Center for Social Investment Studies, for the 14th year in a row.

